@prayank23 

> 1. Is this strictly based on BIP 9 or modified version of BIP 9? If modified, what are the changes and reasons for it?

It's modified it two ways.  First, the timeout is only evaluated at the end of a STARTED period after all signaling blocks in that period have been counted.  This prevents miners from skipping over the signaling period altogether; that's mainly a concern fo

One way to manually run the fuzz tests without running fuzzing is something like this:

```sh
ls ../../../qa-assets/fuzz_seed_corpus/versionbits/* --sort=s -r | 
while read a; do 
  if ! FUZZ=versionbits test/fuzz/fuzz < $a; then
    echo $a;
    echo 'base64:' $(base64 < $a);
    break;
  fi;
done
```

